    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's just more work. more talking, more trying to \"recover,\" more fighting to get back to a baseline that doesn't even feel real anymore. it all feels so performative. like i'm just managing a crisis instead of actually finding any actual stillness. i'm just so exhausted by the idea of having to \"work\" at being okay. sometimes it feels like the only way to truly escape the noise and the weight is to just... stop. just to finally have some actual, permanent quiet.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
